# PVE cluster CA (fortwowlabs/thurgadin) — PUBLIC cert, safe to commit (no private key).
# This is Proxmox's own self-signed cluster CA re-issued with the SAME key/subject/SKI
# but the standards-required keyUsage extension added, because PVE's gen_pveca_cert()
# omits it and strict OpenSSL 3.x (control node) rejects a CA without keyUsage.
# The running hypervisor is unchanged; this is purely the control node's trust anchor.
# Regenerate if PVE ever rotates its cluster CA key:
#   ssh root@<pve> 'faketime yesterday openssl x509 -in /etc/pve/pve-root-ca.pem \
#     -signkey /etc/pve/priv/pve-root-ca.key -days 3650 -set_serial 0x$(openssl rand -hex 8) \
#     -extfile <(printf "basicConstraints=critical,CA:TRUE
keyUsage=critical,keyCertSign,cRLSign,digitalSignature
subjectKeyIdentifier=hash
")'
#
